            <m>\displaystyle y =\frac{x(x^2-1)e^x}{x^3-1}</m>, on the interval  <m>[-2 , 0]</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\displaystyle y =x^2\sin(x^2)</m>, on the interval  <m>[0 ,2 ]</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\displaystyle y =\frac{\ln(x)}{x}</m>, on the interval  <m>[2 ,10 ]</m>
